<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-73E295B0-EA0D-469E-A04F-C6FCE0BEF64F" version="1" lang="en-US"?><tsTroubleshooting xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-73E295B0-EA0D-469E-A04F-C6FCE0BEF64F" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" domains="(topic tsTroubleshooting)                            (topic hi-d)    (topic sdlVariables-c)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c tsTroubleshooting oceTroubleshooting-c)   " class="- topic/topic tsTroubleshooting/tsTroubleshooting "><title class="- topic/title ">12 Media loading fails</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-B87BF88B-91B2-4C27-A55C-91B9B6986C8A"><p class="- topic/p ">Media insertion fails. Roll 2 has more specific symptoms as it has a different paper path. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The normal behavior of the media loading procedure is described in the functional description 12 The function of the media loading drawer section Inserting the media in the media loading drawer. See 
<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="12FUNC03" href="GUID-42DCAC25-3621-40AE-B100-32861107EDF7.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>12 The function of the media loading drawer</xref> 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><tsBody class="- topic/body tsTroubleshooting/tsBody "><tsSymptoms id="GUID-33E1B64A-E818-4500-A780-C8BC692D14B2" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsSymptoms "/><tsCauses id="GUID-C27DF649-C3E4-4AA4-B984-B763DD633869" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p "> The media is not grabbed and not pulled in when the media is fed into the first sensor. No motor activity and no beep.
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-1C0F90F7-CAE4-4FBA-BAA7-919B83A9E5DF" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p "> Check if media feed unit is correctly closed, check sensor 12B11 MLO_DRA1_PINCH1_OPEN_SE
</p></tsDiagnose><tsCauses id="GUID-02F15D59-F5FB-45D5-B2AF-3C3458210BBA" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p "> The media is not grabbed and not pulled in when the media is fed into the first sensor of the media path. The motor activity is audible. 
</p></tsCauses><tsCauses id="GUID-631EB742-EFCA-4329-BFE5-57A7274EA627" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">Obstruction in the media path 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-9ADBECE9-C8F8-4E8C-A07A-A0FDA18E3D9A" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check / Remove the obstruction from the media path. 
</p></tsDiagnose><tsCauses id="GUID-127029F5-0C00-4AF4-8124-AE450B4A8BF6" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">Force of the MLO pinch too low 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-CE58EADD-A113-4C3B-9DE1-BC50BF54F57F" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check / Replace the MLO pinch 
</p></tsDiagnose><tsCauses id="GUID-F75F9750-5D43-487E-B7E4-B69543A6F1F3" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">MLO pinch motor 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-C3AFF485-E86D-4C30-BAB5-AAD847B30CF5" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check / Replace the MLO pinch motor 
</p></tsDiagnose><tsCauses id="GUID-C512D079-C95D-4C59-A115-47EE8A9D3A41" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p "> The media is grabbed and pulled in when the media is fed with a bulge in the media. The bulge makes it possible grab, insert the media, beep and pull back. During media feeding for job media errors occur. 
</p></tsCauses><tsCauses id="GUID-1778636B-610C-4A62-9267-EA4C7BFB5624" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">Force of the MLO pinch too low 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-DE256AD1-A5FE-477A-B490-E150E3289C39" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check / Replace the MLO pinch 
</p></tsDiagnose><tsCauses id="GUID-03711C3A-8E91-4A68-8C0F-F5E14874FA64" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">MLO pinch motor 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-DC8DF05C-CE71-4DB8-AFEE-330BFF527FAB" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check / Replace the MLO pinch motor 
</p></tsDiagnose><tsCauses id="GUID-3A61AEF8-DC3D-47B8-B8E0-185CA8A8EDD4" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p "> Inserting the media of roll 2 into the media path the printer gives the regular beep but the media was not transported into the printer. 
</p></tsCauses><tsCauses id="GUID-8338AFE1-32A5-46F6-A5D2-C34F02E93B08" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">The drive belt of <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 pinch 2 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12M4 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_PINCH2_MO</compsignal></comp> jumps over the teeth. 
</p></tsCauses><tsCauses id="GUID-1DDA75CB-3655-40AE-8B41-B7ED00666272" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">Drive belt tensioner loose 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-1B509343-AA31-4FE2-910F-AB9D84645ED8" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the 2 screws of the drive belt tensioner for <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Media loading drawer 1 pinch 2 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 12M4 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">MLO_DRA1_PINCH2_MO</compsignal></comp> are tightened. 
</p><fig id="GUID-4F27E020-F78F-4F44-9DD2-3E438887B34E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4695DD1F-A543-4CC7-9100-CADF04908246-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4695DD1F-A543-4CC7-9100-CADF04908246-low.png"/></fig></tsDiagnose><tsDiagnose id="GUID-CEBCCB65-5E2D-4809-A878-EC4BBF2D9B69" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check also the tension of the drive belt. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Check / Replace the drive belt. 
</p></tsDiagnose></tsBody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-1DCAF623-68D0-4FB8-99AB-C56278736F96.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
